  "coreIdea": "The minute hand shows the minutes past the hour.",
  "examples": [
    "At 12:15, the minute hand points at 3. 🕐",
    "At 12:30, the minute hand points at 6. 🕐",
    "At 3:30, the minute hand points at 6 and the hour hand is between 3 and 4. 🕐"
  ],
  "misconceptions": [
    "Students may think the minute hand points to the hour number instead of the minute value.",
    "Students may confuse the minute hand with the hour hand when setting.",
    "Students may set the minute hand to 12 for all times."
